{"questionId":"21935844","questionHtml":"<p>Hence, find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></mrow></mfrac><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to integrate at least one term in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>2</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced open=\"|\" close=\"|\"><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for each correct term.</p>\n<p>Award a maximum of <em><strong>M1A1A0A1</strong></em> if modulus signs are omitted.</p>\n<p>Condone the absence of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"21935844","referenceCode":"24M.1.AHL.TZ1.11e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Hence, find ∫1x+122x+1dx.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","AHL 5.15—Further derivatives and indefinite integration of these, partial fractions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}